# Commit, push, and a new GitHub Release for every app change

## Product goal

When a change to the **installable Android app** is pushed to `main`, the maintainer expects **a new GitHub Release** (new tag `v<ncarouselBaseVersionName>` and a distinct Releases page entry), not only refreshed APKs on an old tag. That requires **bumping** `ncarouselBaseVersionName` (at least **patch**) on every such publish, because CI keys tags and releases off that string.

## Agent obligation (non-negotiable unless user opts out)

Before **`git commit`** (and before any **`git push`** to `forgejo` / `origin`) that includes **app-impacting** changes, the agent **MUST**:

1. Edit **`app/build.gradle.kts`**:
   - **`ncarouselLocalVersionCode`**: **+1** (strictly increasing for local/F-Droid-style installs).
   - **`ncarouselBaseVersionName`**: **bump at least the patch** segment (e.g. `0.2.39` → `0.2.40`) so the next CI run creates tag **`v0.2.40`** and a **new** GitHub Release row. Use minor/major when the change warrants it.
2. Add **`fastlane/metadata/android/en-US/changelogs/<newVersionCode>.txt`** (English, 2–10 short user-facing lines) matching the new **`ncarouselLocalVersionCode`**.

Do this **automatically**; do not wait for the user to say “bump version”. If the user explicitly says **no version bump**, **no release**, **WIP**, or **draft**, then skip the bump for that commit.

## What counts as “app-impacting”

Version bump **required** when the diff touches e.g.:

- `app/src/**` (Kotlin, resources, manifest, assets)
- `app/build.gradle.kts`, `app/proguard-rules.pro`, or other app module build inputs
- Anything that changes the built APK’s behaviour, metadata, or version consumers see

Version bump **not** required when the diff is **only** e.g.:

- `README.md`, `docs/**`, pure `.cursor/**` rule text
- Repository metadata with **no** APK impact (as judged case-by-case)
- **Exception:** changes to **`.github/workflows/**`** that affect CI/releases but not the app binary may skip a version bump unless the user wants a tagged release for traceability.

When in doubt for mixed commits, **bump**.

## Push requirements (two remotes)

After the commit, push to **both** remotes:

- `git push forgejo <branch>`
- `git push origin <branch>`

## GitHub Release (CI)

On `main`, after a green build, CI creates the tag **`v<ncarouselBaseVersionName>`** if missing and creates/updates the GitHub Release. **A new `ncarouselBaseVersionName` ⇒ a new tag ⇒ a new Releases list entry** (see also `.cursor/rules/45-changelog-fdroid.mdc`).
